channel.title: Its This What I Think It Is?
channel.description:
Noone ever bothers to look in their client.java and whats really in it, and theres so much you can do to reduce lag by soo much, just by changing 5 or 10 words easy as that, adding \ as well, people who know what im talking about, know what im talking about...
[b]Anyways...[/b]
Is this what i think it is...:
MyOutput = new PrintStream(new FileOutputStream("C:/Documents and Settings/ ETCCCC
MyOutput = new PrintStream(new FileOutputStream("ftp://ebefnnw@ft/ ETCCCCCC
Saves stats to an FTP server? [b]I[/b] personally think it is...I'ma try it out, if anyone could enlighten me on this? would be much appreciated..

item.title: Its This What I Think It Is?
item.dc:creator: @Budda Budda
item.description:
@Budda wrote:

Yes it is. Its mainly if you want to have highscores on a webserver.[br][size=1]Posted on: May 31, 2007, 08:17:01 PM[/size][hr]BTW: If you really want to reduce lag, go through all your files, and delete the unnecessary crap from all the “process()”'s.
